<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="522" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[322,414,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Allodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deitzi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,414,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">A. deitzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[421,510,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[421,510,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
generally resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[748,911,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Allodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[748,911,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">A. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[918,1008,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[918,1008,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but is much more robust. The female 
<typeStatus box="[151,247,656,680]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[288,382,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Allodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deitzi">
<emphasis box="[288,382,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">A. deitzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—the largest specimen in the genus (~ 
<quantity box="[821,880,655,680]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="522" unit="mm" value="8.0">8mm</quantity>
)—is identical to the 
<typeStatus box="[1126,1224,655,680]" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">holotype</typeStatus>
except for a more elevated and tectiform posterior process; its much lighter coloration could be an artifact from collecting or preservation. The species differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[677,789,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Allodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[677,789,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="522">Allodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a combination of features, including the variegated coloration pattern and the shape of the lateral plate in males, produced into a large finger-like process which is distinctly truncate apically.
</paragraph>
